item.title: EU New Car Sales Rise Again
item.description: New passenger-car sales in the EU rose 9.2% in September, the fourteenth consecutive month of growth, with demand for fully electric and hybrid vehicles driving the increase.

item.title: US Treasury Yields Could Fall Faster if Market Steps Up Fed Rate Cut Pricing
item.description: Treasury yields are unlikely to turn decisively lower until markets are prepared to add to future rate cut expectations, “which is unlikely to happen quickly,” SEB Research said.

item.title: U.K. Retail Sales Fall Likely to Disappoint
item.description: Retail sales in the U.K. fell 0.9% in September, with the high cost of living continuing to squeeze consumers.

item.title: Nikkei Falls 0.5%, Dragged by Electronics, Retail Stocks
item.description: Japanese stocks ended lower, dragged by falls in electronics and retail stocks, as concerns persisted over the higher costs of energy and borrowing amid the Middle East conflict.

item.title: Qantas to Increase Fares Due to Higher Fuel Costs
item.description: The Australian airline said it would increase fares, as tensions in the Middle East and a weaker Australian dollar are expected to keep fuel prices high.

item.title: SGD Weakens Vs. USD Amid Rising Geopolitical Tensions
item.description: SGD weakened against USD in the afternoon Asian session amid rising geopolitical tensions.

item.title: Hong Kong Exchanges & Clearing Third-Quarter Profit Rose 30%
item.description: Hong Kong Exchanges & Clearing’s third-quarter net profit saw steady growth, supported by higher net investment income.

item.title: China Restricts Exports of Some Graphite Products
item.description: China’s commerce ministry plans to restrict exports of some graphite products in a bid to protect national security.

item.title: The SEC said it would drop its lawsuit against two cryptocurrency executives who oversaw $1.5 billion in sales of a digital coin known as XRP, in a move that boosts the industry's battle against traditional regulation.
